rComments: If you miss 1 grading criteria on the test you get 0 for that section - it doesnt matter how good you do on the others - overall still below 70. Whereas if you complete all sections, it doesnt matter how bad you wrote it, you can still get 70+ overall Even though no one gets 85+ on tests.. Assignment, participation marks can push you to 85+ overall

MGT428 is not a traditional lecture style. He designed the course in a way that is really taught by the students for the students. Topics are not dry at all since students are presenting it (it would be very boring in a traditional lecture style). Weekly case hand ins require lots of work but does improve your case writing. Overall excellent prof.

Lecture is very slow compared to PT's MGT322 (so it's boring). No case studies. 85-90% of the course is calculation based questions... 10-15% of the course is short answer questions... He tests the same questions every year for MGT426 (but somehow the class avg ends up being C+ even though he does not bellcurve up or down). Overall easy as MGT220
He is a solid professor, does a great job explaining concepts and is very clear with the expectations on graded material.
